47void UpdateEventLogStreamConfig(RtcEventLog* event_log,
48 const AudioSendStream::Config& config,
49 const AudioSendStream::Config* old_config) {
50 using SendCodecSpec = AudioSendStream::Config::SendCodecSpec;
51 // Only update if any of the things we log have changed.
52 auto payload_types_equal = [](const absl::optional<SendCodecSpec>& a,
53 const absl::optional<SendCodecSpec>& b) {
54 if (a.has_value() && b.has_value()) {
55 return a->format.name == b->format.name &&
56 a->payload_type == b->payload_type;
57 }
58 return !a.has_value() && !b.has_value();
59 };
60
61 if (old_config && config.rtp.ssrc == old_config->rtp.ssrc &&
62 config.rtp.extensions == old_config->rtp.extensions &&
63 payload_types_equal(config.send_codec_spec,
64 old_config->send_codec_spec)) {
65 return;
66 }
67
68 auto rtclog_config = std::make_unique<rtclog::StreamConfig>();
69 rtclog_config->local_ssrc = config.rtp.ssrc;
70 rtclog_config->rtp_extensions = config.rtp.extensions;
71 if (config.send_codec_spec) {
72 rtclog_config->codecs.emplace_back(config.send_codec_spec->format.name,
73 config.send_codec_spec->payload_type, 0);
74 }
75 event_log->Log(std::make_unique<RtcEventAudioSendStreamConfig>(
76 std::move(rtclog_config)));
77}
78} // namespace

80constexpr char AudioAllocationConfig::kKey[];
81
82std::unique_ptr<StructParametersParser> AudioAllocationConfig::Parser() {
83 return StructParametersParser::Create( //
84 "min", &min_bitrate, //
85 "max", &max_bitrate, //
86 "prio_rate", &priority_bitrate, //
87 "prio_rate_raw", &priority_bitrate_raw, //
88 "rate_prio", &bitrate_priority);
89}
90
91AudioAllocationConfig::AudioAllocationConfig() {
92 Parser()->Parse(field_trial::FindFullName(kKey));
93 if (priority_bitrate_raw && !priority_bitrate.IsZero()) {
94 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "'priority_bitrate' and '_raw' are mutually "
95 "exclusive but both were configured.";
96 }
97}

134AudioSendStream::AudioSendStream(
135 Clock* clock,
136 const webrtc::AudioSendStream::Config& config,
137 const rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioState>& audio_state,
138 TaskQueueFactory* task_queue_factory,
139 RtpTransportControllerSendInterface* rtp_transport,
140 BitrateAllocatorInterface* bitrate_allocator,
141 RtcEventLog* event_log,
142 const absl::optional<RtpState>& suspended_rtp_state,
143 std::unique_ptr<voe::ChannelSendInterface> channel_send)
144 : clock_(clock),
145 worker_queue_(rtp_transport->GetWorkerQueue()),
146 allocate_audio_without_feedback_(
147 field_trial::IsEnabled("WebRTC-Audio-ABWENoTWCC")),
148 enable_audio_alr_probing_(
149 !field_trial::IsDisabled("WebRTC-Audio-AlrProbing")),
150 send_side_bwe_with_overhead_(
151 !field_trial::IsDisabled("WebRTC-SendSideBwe-WithOverhead")),
152 config_(Config(/*send_transport=*/nullptr)),
153 audio_state_(audio_state),
154 channel_send_(std::move(channel_send)),
155 event_log_(event_log),
156 use_legacy_overhead_calculation_(
157 field_trial::IsEnabled("WebRTC-Audio-LegacyOverhead")),
158 bitrate_allocator_(bitrate_allocator),
159 rtp_transport_(rtp_transport),
160 rtp_rtcp_module_(channel_send_->GetRtpRtcp()),
161 suspended_rtp_state_(suspended_rtp_state) {
162 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "AudioSendStream: " << config.rtp.ssrc;
163 RTC_DCHECK(worker_queue_);
164 RTC_DCHECK(audio_state_);
165 RTC_DCHECK(channel_send_);
166 RTC_DCHECK(bitrate_allocator_);
167 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_transport);
168
169 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_rtcp_module_);
170
171 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
172 ConfigureStream(config, true);
173 UpdateCachedTargetAudioBitrateConstraints();
174 pacer_thread_checker_.Detach();
175}
176
177AudioSendStream::~AudioSendStream() {
178 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
179 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "~AudioSendStream: " << config_.rtp.ssrc;
180 RTC_DCHECK(!sending_);
181 channel_send_->ResetSenderCongestionControlObjects();
182 // Blocking call to synchronize state with worker queue to ensure that there
183 // are no pending tasks left that keeps references to audio.
184 rtc::Event thread_sync_event;
185 worker_queue_->PostTask([&] { thread_sync_event.Set(); });
186 thread_sync_event.Wait(rtc::Event::kForever);
187}

200AudioSendStream::ExtensionIds AudioSendStream::FindExtensionIds(
201 const std::vector<RtpExtension>& extensions) {
202 ExtensionIds ids;
203 for (const auto& extension : extensions) {
204 if (extension.uri == RtpExtension::kAudioLevelUri) {
205 ids.audio_level = extension.id;
206 } else if (extension.uri == RtpExtension::kAbsSendTimeUri) {
207 ids.abs_send_time = extension.id;
208 } else if (extension.uri == RtpExtension::kTransportSequenceNumberUri) {
209 ids.transport_sequence_number = extension.id;
210 } else if (extension.uri == RtpExtension::kMidUri) {
211 ids.mid = extension.id;
212 } else if (extension.uri == RtpExtension::kRidUri) {
213 ids.rid = extension.id;
214 } else if (extension.uri == RtpExtension::kRepairedRidUri) {
215 ids.repaired_rid = extension.id;
216 } else if (extension.uri == RtpExtension::kAbsoluteCaptureTimeUri) {
217 ids.abs_capture_time = extension.id;
218 }
219 }
220 return ids;
221}
222
223int AudioSendStream::TransportSeqNumId(const AudioSendStream::Config& config) {
224 return FindExtensionIds(config.rtp.extensions).transport_sequence_number;
225}
226
227void AudioSendStream::ConfigureStream(
228 const webrtc::AudioSendStream::Config& new_config,
229 bool first_time) {
230 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "AudioSendStream::ConfigureStream: "
231 << new_config.ToString();
232 UpdateEventLogStreamConfig(event_log_, new_config,
233 first_time ? nullptr : &config_);
234
235 const auto& old_config = config_;
236
237 // Configuration parameters which cannot be changed.
238 RTC_DCHECK(first_time ||
239 old_config.send_transport == new_config.send_transport);
240 RTC_DCHECK(first_time || old_config.rtp.ssrc == new_config.rtp.ssrc);
241 if (suspended_rtp_state_ && first_time) {
242 rtp_rtcp_module_->SetRtpState(*suspended_rtp_state_);
243 }
244 if (first_time || old_config.rtp.c_name != new_config.rtp.c_name) {
245 channel_send_->SetRTCP_CNAME(new_config.rtp.c_name);
246 }
247
248 // Enable the frame encryptor if a new frame encryptor has been provided.
249 if (first_time || new_config.frame_encryptor != old_config.frame_encryptor) {
250 channel_send_->SetFrameEncryptor(new_config.frame_encryptor);
251 }
252
253 if (first_time ||
254 new_config.frame_transformer != old_config.frame_transformer) {
255 channel_send_->SetEncoderToPacketizerFrameTransformer(
256 new_config.frame_transformer);
257 }
258
259 if (first_time ||
260 new_config.rtp.extmap_allow_mixed != old_config.rtp.extmap_allow_mixed) {
261 rtp_rtcp_module_->SetExtmapAllowMixed(new_config.rtp.extmap_allow_mixed);
262 }
263
264 const ExtensionIds old_ids = FindExtensionIds(old_config.rtp.extensions);
265 const ExtensionIds new_ids = FindExtensionIds(new_config.rtp.extensions);
266
267 // Audio level indication
268 if (first_time || new_ids.audio_level != old_ids.audio_level) {
269 channel_send_->SetSendAudioLevelIndicationStatus(new_ids.audio_level != 0,
270 new_ids.audio_level);
271 }
272
273 if (first_time || new_ids.abs_send_time != old_ids.abs_send_time) {
274 rtp_rtcp_module_->DeregisterSendRtpHeaderExtension(
275 kRtpExtensionAbsoluteSendTime);
276 if (new_ids.abs_send_time) {
277 rtp_rtcp_module_->RegisterRtpHeaderExtension(AbsoluteSendTime::kUri,
278 new_ids.abs_send_time);
279 }
280 }
281
282 bool transport_seq_num_id_changed =
283 new_ids.transport_sequence_number != old_ids.transport_sequence_number;
284 if (first_time ||
285 (transport_seq_num_id_changed && !allocate_audio_without_feedback_)) {
286 if (!first_time) {
287 channel_send_->ResetSenderCongestionControlObjects();
288 }
289
290 RtcpBandwidthObserver* bandwidth_observer = nullptr;
291
292 if (!allocate_audio_without_feedback_ &&
293 new_ids.transport_sequence_number != 0) {
294 rtp_rtcp_module_->RegisterRtpHeaderExtension(
295 TransportSequenceNumber::kUri, new_ids.transport_sequence_number);
296 // Probing in application limited region is only used in combination with
297 // send side congestion control, wich depends on feedback packets which
298 // requires transport sequence numbers to be enabled.
299 // Optionally request ALR probing but do not override any existing
300 // request from other streams.
301 if (enable_audio_alr_probing_) {
302 rtp_transport_->EnablePeriodicAlrProbing(true);
303 }
304 bandwidth_observer = rtp_transport_->GetBandwidthObserver();
305 }
306 channel_send_->RegisterSenderCongestionControlObjects(rtp_transport_,
307 bandwidth_observer);
308 }
309 // MID RTP header extension.
310 if ((first_time || new_ids.mid != old_ids.mid ||
311 new_config.rtp.mid != old_config.rtp.mid) &&
312 new_ids.mid != 0 && !new_config.rtp.mid.empty()) {
313 rtp_rtcp_module_->RegisterRtpHeaderExtension(RtpMid::kUri, new_ids.mid);
314 rtp_rtcp_module_->SetMid(new_config.rtp.mid);
315 }
316
317 // RID RTP header extension
318 if ((first_time || new_ids.rid != old_ids.rid ||
319 new_ids.repaired_rid != old_ids.repaired_rid ||
320 new_config.rtp.rid != old_config.rtp.rid)) {
321 if (new_ids.rid != 0 || new_ids.repaired_rid != 0) {
322 if (new_config.rtp.rid.empty()) {
323 rtp_rtcp_module_->DeregisterSendRtpHeaderExtension(RtpStreamId::kUri);
324 } else if (new_ids.repaired_rid != 0) {
325 rtp_rtcp_module_->RegisterRtpHeaderExtension(RtpStreamId::kUri,
326 new_ids.repaired_rid);
327 } else {
328 rtp_rtcp_module_->RegisterRtpHeaderExtension(RtpStreamId::kUri,
329 new_ids.rid);
330 }
331 }
332 rtp_rtcp_module_->SetRid(new_config.rtp.rid);
333 }
334
335 if (first_time || new_ids.abs_capture_time != old_ids.abs_capture_time) {
336 rtp_rtcp_module_->DeregisterSendRtpHeaderExtension(
337 kRtpExtensionAbsoluteCaptureTime);
338 if (new_ids.abs_capture_time) {
339 rtp_rtcp_module_->RegisterRtpHeaderExtension(
340 AbsoluteCaptureTimeExtension::kUri, new_ids.abs_capture_time);
341 }
342 }
343
344 if (!ReconfigureSendCodec(new_config)) {
345 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to set up send codec state.";
346 }
347
348 // Set currently known overhead (used in ANA, opus only).
349 {
350 MutexLock lock(&overhead_per_packet_lock_);
351 UpdateOverheadForEncoder();
352 }
353
354 channel_send_->CallEncoder([this](AudioEncoder* encoder) {
355 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
356 if (!encoder) {
357 return;
358 }
359 frame_length_range_ = encoder->GetFrameLengthRange();
360 UpdateCachedTargetAudioBitrateConstraints();
361 });
362
363 if (sending_) {
364 ReconfigureBitrateObserver(new_config);
365 }
366
367 config_ = new_config;
368 if (!first_time) {
369 UpdateCachedTargetAudioBitrateConstraints();
370 }
371}
372
373void AudioSendStream::Start() {
374 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
375 if (sending_) {
376 return;
377 }
378 if (!config_.has_dscp && config_.min_bitrate_bps != -1 &&
379 config_.max_bitrate_bps != -1 &&
380 (allocate_audio_without_feedback_ || TransportSeqNumId(config_) != 0)) {
381 rtp_transport_->AccountForAudioPacketsInPacedSender(true);
382 if (send_side_bwe_with_overhead_)
383 rtp_transport_->IncludeOverheadInPacedSender();
384 rtp_rtcp_module_->SetAsPartOfAllocation(true);
385 ConfigureBitrateObserver();
386 } else {
387 rtp_rtcp_module_->SetAsPartOfAllocation(false);
388 }
389 channel_send_->StartSend();
390 sending_ = true;
391 audio_state()->AddSendingStream(this, encoder_sample_rate_hz_,
392 encoder_num_channels_);
393}
394
395void AudioSendStream::Stop() {
396 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
397 if (!sending_) {
398 return;
399 }
400
401 RemoveBitrateObserver();
402 channel_send_->StopSend();
403 sending_ = false;
404 audio_state()->RemoveSendingStream(this);
405}

407void AudioSendStream::SendAudioData(std::unique_ptr<AudioFrame> audio_frame) {
408 RTC_CHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&audio_capture_race_checker_);
409 RTC_DCHECK_GT(audio_frame->sample_rate_hz_, 0);
410 double duration = static_cast<double>(audio_frame->samples_per_channel_) /
411 audio_frame->sample_rate_hz_;
412 {
413 // Note: SendAudioData() passes the frame further down the pipeline and it
414 // may eventually get sent. But this method is invoked even if we are not
415 // connected, as long as we have an AudioSendStream (created as a result of
416 // an O/A exchange). This means that we are calculating audio levels whether
417 // or not we are sending samples.
418 // TODO(https://crbug.com/webrtc/10771): All "media-source" related stats
419 // should move from send-streams to the local audio sources or tracks; a
420 // send-stream should not be required to read the microphone audio levels.
421 MutexLock lock(&audio_level_lock_);
422 audio_level_.ComputeLevel(*audio_frame, duration);
423 }
424 channel_send_->ProcessAndEncodeAudio(std::move(audio_frame));
425}

445
446webrtc::AudioSendStream::Stats AudioSendStream::GetStats(
447 bool has_remote_tracks) const {
448 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
449 webrtc::AudioSendStream::Stats stats;
450 stats.local_ssrc = config_.rtp.ssrc;
451 stats.target_bitrate_bps = channel_send_->GetBitrate();
452
453 webrtc::CallSendStatistics call_stats = channel_send_->GetRTCPStatistics();
454 stats.payload_bytes_sent = call_stats.payload_bytes_sent;
455 stats.header_and_padding_bytes_sent =
456 call_stats.header_and_padding_bytes_sent;
457 stats.retransmitted_bytes_sent = call_stats.retransmitted_bytes_sent;
458 stats.packets_sent = call_stats.packetsSent;
459 stats.retransmitted_packets_sent = call_stats.retransmitted_packets_sent;
460 // RTT isn't known until a RTCP report is received. Until then, VoiceEngine
461 // returns 0 to indicate an error value.
462 if (call_stats.rttMs > 0) {
463 stats.rtt_ms = call_stats.rttMs;
464 }
465 if (config_.send_codec_spec) {
466 const auto& spec = *config_.send_codec_spec;
467 stats.codec_name = spec.format.name;
468 stats.codec_payload_type = spec.payload_type;
469
470 // Get data from the last remote RTCP report.
471 for (const auto& block : channel_send_->GetRemoteRTCPReportBlocks()) {
472 // Lookup report for send ssrc only.
473 if (block.source_SSRC == stats.local_ssrc) {
474 stats.packets_lost = block.cumulative_num_packets_lost;
475 stats.fraction_lost = Q8ToFloat(block.fraction_lost);
476 // Convert timestamps to milliseconds.
477 if (spec.format.clockrate_hz / 1000 > 0) {
478 stats.jitter_ms =
479 block.interarrival_jitter / (spec.format.clockrate_hz / 1000);
480 }
481 break;
482 }
483 }
484 }
485
486 {
487 MutexLock lock(&audio_level_lock_);
488 stats.audio_level = audio_level_.LevelFullRange();
489 stats.total_input_energy = audio_level_.TotalEnergy();
490 stats.total_input_duration = audio_level_.TotalDuration();
491 }
492
493 stats.typing_noise_detected = audio_state()->typing_noise_detected();
494 stats.ana_statistics = channel_send_->GetANAStatistics();
495
496 AudioProcessing* ap = audio_state_->audio_processing();
497 if (ap) {
498 stats.apm_statistics = ap->GetStatistics(has_remote_tracks);
499 }
500
501 stats.report_block_datas = std::move(call_stats.report_block_datas);
502
503 return stats;
504}
505
506void AudioSendStream::DeliverRtcp(const uint8_t* packet, size_t length) {
507 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
508 channel_send_->ReceivedRTCPPacket(packet, length);
509
510 {
511 // Poll if overhead has changed, which it can do if ack triggers us to stop
512 // sending mid/rid.
513 MutexLock lock(&overhead_per_packet_lock_);
514 UpdateOverheadForEncoder();
515 }
516 UpdateCachedTargetAudioBitrateConstraints();
517}
518
519uint32_t AudioSendStream::OnBitrateUpdated(BitrateAllocationUpdate update) {
520 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_queue_);
521
522 // Pick a target bitrate between the constraints. Overrules the allocator if
523 // it 1) allocated a bitrate of zero to disable the stream or 2) allocated a
524 // higher than max to allow for e.g. extra FEC.
525 RTC_DCHECK(cached_constraints_.has_value());
526 update.target_bitrate.Clamp(cached_constraints_->min,
527 cached_constraints_->max);
528 update.stable_target_bitrate.Clamp(cached_constraints_->min,
529 cached_constraints_->max);
530
531 channel_send_->OnBitrateAllocation(update);
532
533 // The amount of audio protection is not exposed by the encoder, hence
534 // always returning 0.
535 return 0;
536}
537
538void AudioSendStream::SetTransportOverhead(
539 int transport_overhead_per_packet_bytes) {
540 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
541 {
542 MutexLock lock(&overhead_per_packet_lock_);
543 transport_overhead_per_packet_bytes_ = transport_overhead_per_packet_bytes;
544 UpdateOverheadForEncoder();
545 }
546 UpdateCachedTargetAudioBitrateConstraints();
547}
548
549void AudioSendStream::UpdateOverheadForEncoder() {
550 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
551 size_t overhead_per_packet_bytes = GetPerPacketOverheadBytes();
552 if (overhead_per_packet_ == overhead_per_packet_bytes) {
553 return;
554 }
555 overhead_per_packet_ = overhead_per_packet_bytes;
556
557 channel_send_->CallEncoder([&](AudioEncoder* encoder) {
558 encoder->OnReceivedOverhead(overhead_per_packet_bytes);
559 });
560 if (total_packet_overhead_bytes_ != overhead_per_packet_bytes) {
561 total_packet_overhead_bytes_ = overhead_per_packet_bytes;
562 if (registered_with_allocator_) {
563 ConfigureBitrateObserver();
564 }
565 }
566}

568size_t AudioSendStream::TestOnlyGetPerPacketOverheadBytes() const {
569 MutexLock lock(&overhead_per_packet_lock_);
570 return GetPerPacketOverheadBytes();

573size_t AudioSendStream::GetPerPacketOverheadBytes() const {
574 return transport_overhead_per_packet_bytes_ +
575 rtp_rtcp_module_->ExpectedPerPacketOverhead();
576}

610// Apply current codec settings to a single voe::Channel used for sending.
611bool AudioSendStream::SetupSendCodec(const Config& new_config) {
612 RTC_DCHECK(new_config.send_codec_spec);
613 const auto& spec = *new_config.send_codec_spec;
614
615 RTC_DCHECK(new_config.encoder_factory);
616 std::unique_ptr<AudioEncoder> encoder =
617 new_config.encoder_factory->MakeAudioEncoder(
618 spec.payload_type, spec.format, new_config.codec_pair_id);
619
620 if (!encoder) {
621 RTC_DLOG(LS_ERROR) << "Unable to create encoder for "
622 << rtc::ToString(spec.format);
623 return false;
624 }
625
626 // If a bitrate has been specified for the codec, use it over the
627 // codec's default.
628 if (spec.target_bitrate_bps) {
629 encoder->OnReceivedTargetAudioBitrate(*spec.target_bitrate_bps);
630 }
631
632 // Enable ANA if configured (currently only used by Opus).
633 if (new_config.audio_network_adaptor_config) {
634 if (encoder->EnableAudioNetworkAdaptor(
635 *new_config.audio_network_adaptor_config, event_log_)) {
636 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Audio network adaptor enabled on SSRC "
637 << new_config.rtp.ssrc;
638 } else {
639 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Failed to enable Audio network adaptor on SSRC "
640 << new_config.rtp.ssrc;
641 }
642 }
643
644 // Wrap the encoder in an AudioEncoderCNG, if VAD is enabled.
645 if (spec.cng_payload_type) {
646 AudioEncoderCngConfig cng_config;
647 cng_config.num_channels = encoder->NumChannels();
648 cng_config.payload_type = *spec.cng_payload_type;
649 cng_config.speech_encoder = std::move(encoder);
650 cng_config.vad_mode = Vad::kVadNormal;
651 encoder = CreateComfortNoiseEncoder(std::move(cng_config));
652
653 RegisterCngPayloadType(*spec.cng_payload_type,
654 new_config.send_codec_spec->format.clockrate_hz);
655 }
656
657 // Wrap the encoder in a RED encoder, if RED is enabled.
658 if (spec.red_payload_type) {
659 AudioEncoderCopyRed::Config red_config;
660 red_config.payload_type = *spec.red_payload_type;
661 red_config.speech_encoder = std::move(encoder);
662 encoder = std::make_unique<AudioEncoderCopyRed>(std::move(red_config));
663 }
664
665 // Set currently known overhead (used in ANA, opus only).
666 // If overhead changes later, it will be updated in UpdateOverheadForEncoder.
667 {
668 MutexLock lock(&overhead_per_packet_lock_);
669 size_t overhead = GetPerPacketOverheadBytes();
670 if (overhead > 0) {
671 encoder->OnReceivedOverhead(overhead);
672 }
673 }
674
675 StoreEncoderProperties(encoder->SampleRateHz(), encoder->NumChannels());
676 channel_send_->SetEncoder(new_config.send_codec_spec->payload_type,
677 std::move(encoder));
678
679 return true;
680}
681
682bool AudioSendStream::ReconfigureSendCodec(const Config& new_config) {
683 const auto& old_config = config_;
684
685 if (!new_config.send_codec_spec) {
686 // We cannot de-configure a send codec. So we will do nothing.
687 // By design, the send codec should have not been configured.
688 RTC_DCHECK(!old_config.send_codec_spec);
689 return true;
690 }
691
692 if (new_config.send_codec_spec == old_config.send_codec_spec &&
693 new_config.audio_network_adaptor_config ==
694 old_config.audio_network_adaptor_config) {
695 return true;
696 }
697
698 // If we have no encoder, or the format or payload type's changed, create a
699 // new encoder.
700 if (!old_config.send_codec_spec ||
701 new_config.send_codec_spec->format !=
702 old_config.send_codec_spec->format ||
703 new_config.send_codec_spec->payload_type !=
704 old_config.send_codec_spec->payload_type) {
705 return SetupSendCodec(new_config);
706 }
707
708 const absl::optional<int>& new_target_bitrate_bps =
709 new_config.send_codec_spec->target_bitrate_bps;
710 // If a bitrate has been specified for the codec, use it over the
711 // codec's default.
712 if (new_target_bitrate_bps &&
713 new_target_bitrate_bps !=
714 old_config.send_codec_spec->target_bitrate_bps) {
715 channel_send_->CallEncoder([&](AudioEncoder* encoder) {
716 encoder->OnReceivedTargetAudioBitrate(*new_target_bitrate_bps);
717 });
718 }
719
720 ReconfigureANA(new_config);
721 ReconfigureCNG(new_config);
722
723 return true;
724}
725
726void AudioSendStream::ReconfigureANA(const Config& new_config) {
727 if (new_config.audio_network_adaptor_config ==
728 config_.audio_network_adaptor_config) {
729 return;
730 }
731 if (new_config.audio_network_adaptor_config) {
732 // This lock needs to be acquired before CallEncoder, since it aquires
733 // another lock and we need to maintain the same order at all call sites to
734 // avoid deadlock.
735 MutexLock lock(&overhead_per_packet_lock_);
736 size_t overhead = GetPerPacketOverheadBytes();
737 channel_send_->CallEncoder([&](AudioEncoder* encoder) {
738 if (encoder->EnableAudioNetworkAdaptor(
739 *new_config.audio_network_adaptor_config, event_log_)) {
740 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Audio network adaptor enabled on SSRC "
741 << new_config.rtp.ssrc;
742 if (overhead > 0) {
743 encoder->OnReceivedOverhead(overhead);
744 }
745 } else {
746 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Failed to enable Audio network adaptor on SSRC "
747 << new_config.rtp.ssrc;
748 }
749 });
750 } else {
751 channel_send_->CallEncoder(
752 [&](AudioEncoder* encoder) { encoder->DisableAudioNetworkAdaptor(); });
753 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Audio network adaptor disabled on SSRC "
754 << new_config.rtp.ssrc;
755 }
756}
757
758void AudioSendStream::ReconfigureCNG(const Config& new_config) {
759 if (new_config.send_codec_spec->cng_payload_type ==
760 config_.send_codec_spec->cng_payload_type) {
761 return;
762 }
763
764 // Register the CNG payload type if it's been added, don't do anything if CNG
765 // is removed. Payload types must not be redefined.
766 if (new_config.send_codec_spec->cng_payload_type) {
767 RegisterCngPayloadType(*new_config.send_codec_spec->cng_payload_type,
768 new_config.send_codec_spec->format.clockrate_hz);
769 }
770
771 // Wrap or unwrap the encoder in an AudioEncoderCNG.
772 channel_send_->ModifyEncoder([&](std::unique_ptr<AudioEncoder>* encoder_ptr) {
773 std::unique_ptr<AudioEncoder> old_encoder(std::move(*encoder_ptr));
774 auto sub_encoders = old_encoder->ReclaimContainedEncoders();
775 if (!sub_encoders.empty()) {
776 // Replace enc with its sub encoder. We need to put the sub
777 // encoder in a temporary first, since otherwise the old value
778 // of enc would be destroyed before the new value got assigned,
779 // which would be bad since the new value is a part of the old
780 // value.
781 auto tmp = std::move(sub_encoders[0]);
782 old_encoder = std::move(tmp);
783 }
784 if (new_config.send_codec_spec->cng_payload_type) {
785 AudioEncoderCngConfig config;
786 config.speech_encoder = std::move(old_encoder);
787 config.num_channels = config.speech_encoder->NumChannels();
788 config.payload_type = *new_config.send_codec_spec->cng_payload_type;
789 config.vad_mode = Vad::kVadNormal;
790 *encoder_ptr = CreateComfortNoiseEncoder(std::move(config));
791 } else {
792 *encoder_ptr = std::move(old_encoder);
793 }
794 });
795}
796
797void AudioSendStream::ReconfigureBitrateObserver(
798 const webrtc::AudioSendStream::Config& new_config) {
799 // Since the Config's default is for both of these to be -1, this test will
800 // allow us to configure the bitrate observer if the new config has bitrate
801 // limits set, but would only have us call RemoveBitrateObserver if we were
802 // previously configured with bitrate limits.
803 if (config_.min_bitrate_bps == new_config.min_bitrate_bps &&
804 config_.max_bitrate_bps == new_config.max_bitrate_bps &&
805 config_.bitrate_priority == new_config.bitrate_priority &&
806 TransportSeqNumId(config_) == TransportSeqNumId(new_config) &&
807 config_.audio_network_adaptor_config ==
808 new_config.audio_network_adaptor_config) {
809 return;
810 }
811
812 if (!new_config.has_dscp && new_config.min_bitrate_bps != -1 &&
813 new_config.max_bitrate_bps != -1 && TransportSeqNumId(new_config) != 0) {
814 rtp_transport_->AccountForAudioPacketsInPacedSender(true);
815 if (send_side_bwe_with_overhead_)
816 rtp_transport_->IncludeOverheadInPacedSender();
817 // We may get a callback immediately as the observer is registered, so
818 // make sure the bitrate limits in config_ are up-to-date.
819 config_.min_bitrate_bps = new_config.min_bitrate_bps;
820 config_.max_bitrate_bps = new_config.max_bitrate_bps;
821
822 config_.bitrate_priority = new_config.bitrate_priority;
823 ConfigureBitrateObserver();
824 rtp_rtcp_module_->SetAsPartOfAllocation(true);
825 } else {
826 rtp_transport_->AccountForAudioPacketsInPacedSender(false);
827 RemoveBitrateObserver();
828 rtp_rtcp_module_->SetAsPartOfAllocation(false);
829 }
830}
831
832void AudioSendStream::ConfigureBitrateObserver() {
833 // This either updates the current observer or adds a new observer.
834 // TODO(srte): Add overhead compensation here.
835 auto constraints = GetMinMaxBitrateConstraints();
836 RTC_DCHECK(constraints.has_value());
837
838 DataRate priority_bitrate = allocation_settings_.priority_bitrate;
839 if (send_side_bwe_with_overhead_) {
840 if (use_legacy_overhead_calculation_) {
841 // OverheadPerPacket = Ipv4(20B) + UDP(8B) + SRTP(10B) + RTP(12)
842 constexpr int kOverheadPerPacket = 20 + 8 + 10 + 12;
843 const TimeDelta kMinPacketDuration = TimeDelta::Millis(20);
844 DataRate max_overhead =
845 DataSize::Bytes(kOverheadPerPacket) / kMinPacketDuration;
846 priority_bitrate += max_overhead;
847 } else {
848 RTC_DCHECK(frame_length_range_);
849 const DataSize overhead_per_packet =
850 DataSize::Bytes(total_packet_overhead_bytes_);
851 DataRate min_overhead = overhead_per_packet / frame_length_range_->second;
852 priority_bitrate += min_overhead;
853 }
854 }
855 if (allocation_settings_.priority_bitrate_raw)
856 priority_bitrate = *allocation_settings_.priority_bitrate_raw;
857
858 worker_queue_->PostTask([this, constraints, priority_bitrate,
859 config_bitrate_priority = config_.bitrate_priority] {
860 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_queue_);
861 bitrate_allocator_->AddObserver(
862 this,
863 MediaStreamAllocationConfig{
864 constraints->min.bps<uint32_t>(), constraints->max.bps<uint32_t>(),
865 0, priority_bitrate.bps(), true,
866 allocation_settings_.bitrate_priority.value_or(
867 config_bitrate_priority)});
868 });
869 registered_with_allocator_ = true;
870}
871
872void AudioSendStream::RemoveBitrateObserver() {
873 registered_with_allocator_ = false;
874 rtc::Event thread_sync_event;
875 worker_queue_->PostTask([this, &thread_sync_event] {
876 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_queue_);
877 bitrate_allocator_->RemoveObserver(this);
878 thread_sync_event.Set();
879 });
880 thread_sync_event.Wait(rtc::Event::kForever);
881}
882
883absl::optional<AudioSendStream::TargetAudioBitrateConstraints>
884AudioSendStream::GetMinMaxBitrateConstraints() const {
885 if (config_.min_bitrate_bps < 0 || config_.max_bitrate_bps < 0) {
886 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Config is invalid: min_bitrate_bps="
887 << config_.min_bitrate_bps
888 << "; max_bitrate_bps=" << config_.max_bitrate_bps
889 << "; both expected greater or equal to 0";
890 return absl::nullopt;
891 }
892 TargetAudioBitrateConstraints constraints{
893 DataRate::BitsPerSec(config_.min_bitrate_bps),
894 DataRate::BitsPerSec(config_.max_bitrate_bps)};
895
896 // If bitrates were explicitly overriden via field trial, use those values.
897 if (allocation_settings_.min_bitrate)
898 constraints.min = *allocation_settings_.min_bitrate;
899 if (allocation_settings_.max_bitrate)
900 constraints.max = *allocation_settings_.max_bitrate;
901
902 RTC_DCHECK_GE(constraints.min, DataRate::Zero());
903 RTC_DCHECK_GE(constraints.max, DataRate::Zero());
904 if (constraints.max < constraints.min) {
905 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "TargetAudioBitrateConstraints::max is less than "
906 << "TargetAudioBitrateConstraints::min";
907 return absl::nullopt;
908 }
909 if (send_side_bwe_with_overhead_) {
910 if (use_legacy_overhead_calculation_) {
911 // OverheadPerPacket = Ipv4(20B) + UDP(8B) + SRTP(10B) + RTP(12)
912 const DataSize kOverheadPerPacket = DataSize::Bytes(20 + 8 + 10 + 12);
913 const TimeDelta kMaxFrameLength =
914 TimeDelta::Millis(60); // Based on Opus spec
915 const DataRate kMinOverhead = kOverheadPerPacket / kMaxFrameLength;
916 constraints.min += kMinOverhead;
917 constraints.max += kMinOverhead;
918 } else {
919 if (!frame_length_range_.has_value()) {
920 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "frame_length_range_ is not set";
921 return absl::nullopt;
922 }
923 const DataSize kOverheadPerPacket =
924 DataSize::Bytes(total_packet_overhead_bytes_);
925 constraints.min += kOverheadPerPacket / frame_length_range_->second;
926 constraints.max += kOverheadPerPacket / frame_length_range_->first;
927 }
928 }
929 return constraints;
930}
931
932void AudioSendStream::RegisterCngPayloadType(int payload_type,
933 int clockrate_hz) {
934 channel_send_->RegisterCngPayloadType(payload_type, clockrate_hz);
935}
936
937void AudioSendStream::UpdateCachedTargetAudioBitrateConstraints() {
938 absl::optional<AudioSendStream::TargetAudioBitrateConstraints>
939 new_constraints = GetMinMaxBitrateConstraints();
940 if (!new_constraints.has_value()) {
941 return;
942 }
943 worker_queue_->PostTask([this, new_constraints]() {
944 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_queue_);
945 cached_constraints_ = new_constraints;
946 });
947}
